      "patient_reported_reason": "Asthma review and eczema flare",
      "clinician_notes": "Subjective: 34-year-old female for annual asthma review. Reports good control in the last 3 months — no night waking, no oral steroid courses. AQLQ score 5.8. However, presenting with bilateral flexural eczema flare affecting antecubital fossae and popliteal fossae for 2 weeks. No infection signs.\n\nObjective: SpO2 98% on RA. Peak flow 420 L/min (98% predicted). Chest clear. Bilateral flexural erythema and lichenification consistent with atopic dermatitis, no secondary infection.\n\nAssessment: Well-controlled asthma. Eczema flare — likely triggered by cold dry weather.\n\nPlan: Continue Symbicort 200/6 mcg BD + Ventolin PRN. Add Eumovate 0.05% cream to affected areas BD during flare, then reduce to OD when improving. Emollient regularly. Review in 3 months. Note penicillin allergy on record — any future infections require non-penicillin alternatives.",
